# WorkflowAsList Commit Workflow
# Purpose: Guide Conventional Commits for workflow-as-list project
# Usage: workflow run workflow/commit.workflow.list
# Reference: .github/COMMIT_CONVENTION.md
# NOTE: Self-hosted (project-specific), not generic template

# WHY: Show actual changed files for informed type selection
# NOTE: Command output provides factual basis, not memory-based judgment
- (analyze) Analyze changed files with git diff --cached --name-only
  - Run: git diff --cached --name-only
  - Show: Changed files list (use for type selection below)

# WHY: Ensure clean changes before composing message
# NOTE: Check for .env files and debug statements (common mistakes)
- (start) Validate no sensitive files are committed
  - Ask: Ready to commit? (yes/no, fix issues first if no)
  - @start[1]: Ready?

# WHY: Header is required per spec, type determines version bump (feat->MINOR, fix->PATCH)
# NOTE: Only src/ changes trigger version (feat/fix), others use chore/docs/test
# REFERENCE: .github/COMMIT_CONVENTION.md
# PROJECT RULES: src/->feat/fix | tests/->test | workflow/->chore | examples/->docs | .github/->ci | scripts/->chore
- (header) Compose commit message header following Conventional Commits format: type[scope]: description
  - Show: Changed files from (analyze) step
  - Recommend: Type based on PROJECT RULES above
  - Ask: Type? (feat/fix/test/docs/chore/ci/refactor/style)
  - Ask: Scope? (optional: cli/executor/security/parser/server, skip if unclear)
  - Ask: Description? (imperative mood, lowercase start, no period, under 72 characters)
  - Show: Complete format is:
    <type>(<scope>): <description>
    
    [optional body - separate paragraph]
    
    [optional footer - BREAKING CHANGE: / Closes #]

# WHY: Body explains WHY not WHAT, optional for complex changes
# NOTE: Wrap at 72 characters, use for motivation and alternatives
- (body) Ask if body is needed for complex changes that require explanation
  - Ask: Need body? (yes/no, yes if change needs context or motivation)
  - If yes: Ask: Body content? (explain motivation, alternatives considered, assumptions)

# WHY: BREAKING CHANGE triggers MAJOR version, issue links close tickets
# NOTE: Footer is optional, use when applicable
- (footer) Ask if footer is needed for BREAKING CHANGE or issue links
  - Ask: Breaking API change? (yes -> add BREAKING CHANGE: <description> in footer)
  - Ask: Issue to close? (yes -> add Closes #<number> in footer)

# WHY: Final review before irreversible action
# NOTE: Full format has header, blank line, body (optional), blank line, footer (optional)
- (confirm) Show full formatted commit message with header, body (if any), and footer (if any), ask for final confirmation
  - Ask: Confirm and execute git commit? (yes/no)
  - @confirm[1]: Confirmed?
  - Execute: git commit -m "<full message>"
  - Show: Commit hash with git rev-parse --short HEAD

- End
